heisigStory: We use the Roman numeral II here to stress that this kanji is an older form of the kanji for two. Think of two arrows in a quiver, standing up like the numeral II.
koohiiStory1: II (older form of writing 2). After shooting one arrow (the dash top left), I have 2 arrows left in my quiver (bottom left).
koohiiStory2: Once you have two old arrows left in your quiver, you better start running...!
myStory: đôi cặp 2. một thành hai là có đôi
